Installing CLI:

Simply copy the file CLI.ACC to the Root Directory of a disk. The
Root Directory is the directory that is displayed when your ST boots
up e.g. The Name CLI.ACC should be displayed when your ST has finished
booting up.

Using CLI:

Simply click on the DESK menu and again on the Command Interface
option. You are now in the Command Line Interpretor. This enables DOS
commands to be entered directly into the computer without accessing
GEM. Pressing the HELP key will display all the commands available to
you. Typing QUIT will return you to the desktop.

